  "solution": [
    "## Solutions to Matrix Inverse Exercises",
    "",
    "### Exercise 1: 2×2 Matrix Inverse Formula",
    "",
    "**a)** A = $$\\begin{pmatrix} 1 & 2 \\\\ 3 & 4 \\end{pmatrix}$$, det(A) = 1×4 - 2×3 = -2 ≠ 0",
    "A⁻¹ = (1/-2) × $$\\begin{pmatrix} 4 & -2 \\\\ -3 & 1 \\end{pmatrix}$$ = -1/2 × $$\\begin{pmatrix} 4 & -2 \\\\ -3 & 1 \\end{pmatrix}$$ = $$\\begin{pmatrix} -2 & 1 \\\\ 3/2 & -1/2 \\end{pmatrix}$$",
    "",
    "**b)** B = $$\\begin{pmatrix} 4 & 2 \\\\ 3 & 1 \\end{pmatrix}$$, det(B) = 4×1 - 2×3 = 4-6 = -2 ≠ 0",
    "B⁻¹ = (1/-2) × $$\\begin{pmatrix} 1 & -2 \\\\ -3 & 4 \\end{pmatrix}$$ = -1/2 × $$\\begin{pmatrix} 1 & -2 \\\\ -3 & 4 \\end{pmatrix}$$ = $$\\begin{pmatrix} -1/2 & 1 \\\\ 3/2 & -2 \\end{pmatrix}$$",
    "",
    "**c)** C = $$\\begin{pmatrix} 2 & -1 \\\\ 1 & 3 \\end{pmatrix}$$, det(C) = 2×3 - (-1)×1 = 6+1 = 7 ≠ 0",
    "C⁻¹ = (1/7) × $$\\begin{pmatrix} 3 & 1 \\\\ -1 & 2 \\end{pmatrix}$$ = $$\\begin{pmatrix} 3/7 & 1/7 \\\\ -1/7 & 2/7 \\end{pmatrix}$$",
    "",
    "**d)** General 2×2: A⁻¹ = (1/(ad-bc)) × $$\\begin{pmatrix} d & -b \\\\ -c & a \\end{pmatrix}$$",
    "",
    "### Exercise 2: Verification of Inverse",
    "",
    "**a)** A × A⁻¹ = $$\\begin{pmatrix} 1 & 2 \\\\ 3 & 4 \\end{pmatrix}$$ × $$\\begin{pmatrix} -2 & 1 \\\\ 1.5 & -0.5 \\end{pmatrix}$$ = $$\\begin{pmatrix} 1×(-2)+2×1.5 & 1×1+2×(-0.5) \\\\ 3×(-2)+4×1.5 & 3×1+4×(-0.5) \\end{pmatrix}$$ = $$\\begin{pmatrix} -2+3 & 1-1 \\\\ -6+6 & 3-2 \\end{pmatrix}$$ = $$\\begin{pmatrix} 1 & 0 \\\\ 0 & 1 \\end{pmatrix}$$ ✓",
    "",
    "**b)** B × B⁻¹ = I (verification similar to above) ✓",
    "",
    "**c)** C × C⁻¹ = I (verification similar to above) ✓",
    "",
    "### Exercise 3: Properties of Matrix Inverse",
    "",
    "**a)** (A⁻¹)⁻¹ = A: Using A from exercise 1a, A⁻¹ = $$\\begin{pmatrix} -2 & 1 \\\\ 1.5 & -0.5 \\end{pmatrix}$$, then (A⁻¹)⁻¹ = A ✓",
    "",
    "**b)** (AB)⁻¹ = B⁻¹A⁻¹: Let A and B be from exercise 1a and 1b, compute both sides and verify equality ✓",
    "",
    "**c)** (Aᵀ)⁻¹ = (A⁻¹)ᵀ: Take transpose of both sides and verify ✓",
    "",
    "**d)** det(A⁻¹) = 1/det(A): For A with det(A) = -2, det(A⁻¹) = 1/(-2) = -0.5 ✓",
    "",
    "### Exercise 4: Inverse of Elementary Matrices",
    "",
    "**a)** E⁻¹ = E (since E×E = I) ✓",
    "",
    "**b)** F⁻¹ = $$\\begin{pmatrix} 1/3 & 0 \\\\ 0 & 1 \\end{pmatrix}$$ ✓",
    "",
    "**c)** G⁻¹ = $$\\begin{pmatrix} 1 & 0 \\\\ -2 & 1 \\end{pmatrix}$$ ✓",
    "",
    "### Exercise 5: When Does a Matrix Have an Inverse?",
    "",
    "**a)** det(A) = -2 ≠ 0, invertible ✓",
    "",
    "**b)** det(B) = 1×4 - 2×2 = 0, not invertible ❌",
    "",
    "**c)** det(C) = 0×0 - 1×1 = -1 ≠ 0, invertible ✓",
    "",
    "**d)** det(D) = 2×2 - 3×1 = 1 ≠ 0, invertible ✓",
    "",
